  it("uses a shell-agnostic printenv PATH probe", () => {
    const execFile = vi.fn<(...)>(() => "__T3CODE_PATH_START__\n/a:/b\n__T3CODE_PATH_END__\n");
    expect(readPathFromLoginShell("/opt/homebrew/bin/fish", execFile)).toBe("/a:/b");
  });
});
```

---

### 7. DEPENDENCY MANAGEMENT

**packages/shared package.json:**

```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "@t3tools/contracts": "workspace:*",
    "effect": "catalog:"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@effect/language-service": "catalog:",
    "@effect/vitest": "catalog:",
    "@types/node": "catalog:",
    "typescript": "catalog:",
    "vitest": "catalog:"
  }
}
```

- Uses `workspace:*` for local package references
- Uses `catalog:` for unified dependency versions (managed centrally)
- Core dependencies: Effect library for functional programming
- Testing: vitest with @effect/vitest for Effect-based tests

---

### SUMMARY TABLE

| Aspect | packages/shared | packages/contracts |
|--------|-----------------|-------------------|
| **Exports** | Explicit subpaths (./git, ./model, etc.) | Single barrel (.) with re-exports |
| **Module Organization** | Single .ts files, one-to-one with exports | src/index.ts + feature modules |
| **Build Output** | Direct source (no dist) | Built dist/ (ESM + CJS via tsdown) |
| **Naming (files)** | Matches export name exactly | index.ts + feature modules |
| **Class/Function Balance** | Mix of both | Mostly schemas (functions) |
| **Schema Library** | None in shared | Effect Schema throughout |
| **Service Pattern** | Effect-based services with layers | Data schemas with branded types |
| **Test Framework** | vitest + @effect/vitest | vitest + @effect/vitest |

---

### KEY FILES REFERENCED

- `/packages/shared/package.json` - Subpath exports definition
- `/packages/shared/tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (extends base)
- `/tsconfig.base.json` - Root TypeScript configuration
- `/packages/shared/src/model.ts` - Utility functions with overloads
- `/packages/shared/src/git.ts` - String sanitization utilities
- `/packages/shared/src/Net.ts` - Effect-based service pattern
- `/packages/shared/src/logging.ts` - Class-based implementation
- `/packages/contracts/src/baseSchemas.ts` - Branded type pattern
- `/packages/contracts/src/model.ts` - Literal union + const satisfies pattern
- `/packages/contracts/src/git.ts` - Domain types + RPC input schemas
- `/packages/contracts/src/index.ts` - Barrel export pattern

